5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to county subdivision regulations; to amend
10 Section 11-24-2, Code of Alabama 1975; to limit the period
11 during which a transfer of land to an immediate family member
12 is exempt from subdivision regulations to 24 months; and to
13 make nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update the
14 existing code language to current style.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
16 Section 1. Section 11-24-2, Code of Alabama 1975, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 "§11-24-2
19 (a) It shall be the duty of the owner and developer of
20 each subdivision to have complete all construction completed
21 in conformity with this chapter and, prior to beginning any
22 construction or development, to submit the proposed plat to
23 the county commission for approval and to obtain a permit to
24 develop as required in this section. The permit to develop
25 shall be obtained before the actual sale, offering for sale,
26 transfer, or lease of any lots from the subdivision or
27 addition to the public, it and must include a plan to deliver
28 utilities including water., and The permit to develop shall
